  "text": "The alerting evaluation scheduler tick and overrun detection are implemented across four key files in the `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule` package.\n\n**Scheduler tick loop** (`pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go`):\n- `schedulePeriodic()` is the main scheduler loop. It receives ticks from the ticker (`case tick := <-t.C`) and calls `processTick()` on each tick. It also measures `BehindSeconds` — the lag between the wall-clock time and the expected tick time — as an early indicator of overrun.\n- `processTick()` determines which alert rules are due for evaluation on the current tick (based on `tickNum % itemFrequency == offset`), builds a list of `readyToRunItem` entries, and dispatches them via `runJobFn()`.\n- `runJobFn()` is where **overrun detection** happens: it calls `alertRule.Eval()`, which does a non-blocking drain of the rule's `evalCh` channel before sending the new evaluation. If a previous evaluation was still pending (i.e., the channel was not empty), `Eval()` returns the dropped evaluation as its second return value. `runJobFn()` checks `if dropped != nil` and logs the warning **\"Tick dropped because alert rule evaluation is too slow\"**, then increments the `EvaluationMissed` Prometheus counter.\n\n**Per-rule evaluation routine** (`pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go`):\n- `alertRule.Eval()` implements the overrun detection at the rule level. Before sending a new evaluation signal into `evalCh`, it does a non-blocking read to drain any already-queued evaluation. If one is found, it is returned as the 'dropped' value, signalling to the scheduler that the previous cycle overran.\n- `alertRule.Run()` is the per-rule goroutine that waits on `evalCh` and calls `evaluate()` to perform the actual rule evaluation.\n\n**Ticker** (`pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go`):\n- `ticker.T.run()` emits ticks at regular interval marks. Unlike `time.Ticker`, it does NOT drop ticks for slow receivers — it queues them. This means the scheduler can observe how many ticks have accumulated (i.e., how far behind it is), which is the foundation for overrun detection.\n\n**Metrics** (`pkg/services/ngalert/metrics/scheduler.go`):\n- `BehindSeconds` gauge: set in `schedulePeriodic()` as `start.Sub(tick).Seconds()`, measuring how many seconds the scheduler is behind the expected tick time.\n- `EvaluationMissed` counter vec: incremented in `runJobFn()` whenever a tick is dropped due to a slow rule evaluation, labelled by org and rule title. This corresponds to the Prometheus metric `grafana_alerting_schedule_rule_evaluations_missed_total`."
}

